snippet.textDisplay: You can love someone and cheat, I think. Cheating in this case is not ethical (if you're in a healthy relationship with the person you're with), but you may be chasing validation from others, you may be confused or bored and unsure as to why or how to make your relationship exciting, you may be chasing excitement, or you may be drunk/high. These are temporary emotions, and cheating is a way to cope temporarily, but the damage is long lasting. It isnt worth it.
snippet.textOriginal: You can love someone and cheat, I think. Cheating in this case is not ethical (if you're in a healthy relationship with the person you're with), but you may be chasing validation from others, you may be confused or bored and unsure as to why or how to make your relationship exciting, you may be chasing excitement, or you may be drunk/high. These are temporary emotions, and cheating is a way to cope temporarily, but the damage is long lasting. It isnt worth it.

snippet.textDisplay: I’m properly going to get a lot of hate for this but sometimes cheating can help a relationship. I’m not saying that’s an excuse to do it, but if afterwards the person feels remorse and guilt for their actions or maybe it helps them understand where their relationship has been going wrong, this can mend relationships. I’ve seen it happen and it has been genuinely beneficial.

snippet.textDisplay: You can definitely have a good reason to cheat. It is not always safe to leave a toxic or dangerous relationship. It isnt as easy as "breaking up" with the othet person, or running away from the house you share. If you aren't safe, its okay to desire a romantic, sensual and sexual safe space- away from what happens with your partner. And once its safe, break up and leave them as soon as humanly possible.

snippet.textDisplay:
When people have done awful things, but regret them and understand how it hurt someone. You can tell.
In this video, no one fit that bill. That's cheating for you.
It's selfish. Its self entitled. It shows the world you are an asshole.
In 99.5% of cheating cases, you could have broken up with the person before cheating or even considering cheating. But you didn't. Because you're awful. Because you're selfish. Because you're an asshole.

I would like to say to people who think cheating is always wrong. Well no. Cheating is wrong when you can break up with someone. There are many cases where that's not possible: abusive partner who you are threatened by, arranged marriages, country with marriages you can't divorce/get out of, etc.
